          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript for private or public consultation and recitation related to the mythology and worship (pūjā) of the elephant-headed, Hindu deity Gaṇeśa and particularly the form of Bhālacandra (one with the moon in his forehead) or Bhālacandravināyaka, popular in the state of Maharashtra. Speakers are Pārvatī, Gaṇeśa, and Kulāla. Possibly from the Gaṇeśapurāṇa. Manuscript is unfinished.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
